-descendent stories she grew up with while paying respects to her father and documenting the censorship she faces from her mother, loyal still to the pioneer myth of the early twentieth century. It is only when both parents are gone that Morgan is liberated to write a story of reckoning on the northern Great Plains.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezGreat Plains. 0aIndigenous peopleszGreat PlainsxHistoryy20th century. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Personal Memoirs.2bisacsh  aA Geography of Blood.  aSaskatchewan.  aSharon Butala.  acreative non-fiction.  aexperimental writing.  afamily tragedy.  agreat plains.  amagical realism.  amemoir.  aprose fiction.  asettler colonialism.  atreaty 4.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889778580423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889778580/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles